-align: center;\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.bradford.ac.uk\/scholarships\/info\/uk-academic-excellence-scholarships-2024\" class=\"broken_link\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">View Scholarship<\/a><\/p>\n<hr \/>\n<h4 id=\"33-university-of-bradford-sanctuary-scholarship\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"33_University_of_Bradford_Sanctuary_Scholarship\"><\/span><strong>33. University of Bradford Sanctuary Scholarship<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Prospective students<\/li>\n<li>Undergraduate<\/li>\n<li>Postgraduate taught<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.bradford.ac.uk\/scholarships\/info\/Sanctuary-Scholarship-2024\" class=\"broken_link\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">View Scholarship<\/a><\/p>\n<hr \/>\n<h2 id=\"eligibility-criteria\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Eligibility_Criteria\"><\/span><strong>Eligibility Criteria:<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>To be eligible for the <strong>University of Bradford Scholarship,<\/strong> applicants need to fulfil the following criteria:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Students with <strong>any nationality<\/strong>\u00a0are eligible to apply.<\/li>\n<li>Black students<\/li>\n<li>Disabled students<\/li>\n<li>Female students<\/li>\n<li>Care leavers<\/li>\n<li>Polar Q1 and Q2 students<\/li>\n<li>Refugees given the sanctuary status of the university<\/li>\n<li>Estranged students<\/li>\n<li>Gypsy, Roma, and Traveller students<\/li>\n<li>Children from military families, veterans and partners of military personnel.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p><strong>Prioritizing criteria in case of over-subscription:<\/strong><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Students with 2 or more underrepresented group characteristics.<\/li>\n<li>Care leavers are based on the rationale that they are the most underrepresented group within the University of Bradford and underrepresented in highly skilled employment.<\/li>\n<li>Black students are based on the rationale that they are the 2nd most underrepresented group within the University of Bradford and underrepresented in highly skilled employment.<\/li>\n<li>Disabled students are based on the rationale that they are the 3rd most underrepresented group within the University of Bradford and underrepresented in highly skilled employment.<\/li>\n<li>Female students are based on the rationale that they are underrepresented in the digital sector, although not underrepresented within the student body at the University of Bradford.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h3 id=\"documents-required\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Documents_Required\"><\/span><strong>Documents Required:<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>Applicants have to prepare the following document while applying online for the <strong>University of Bradford Scholarship in the UK<\/strong>:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Documents:\u00a0<\/strong>You must provide additional information to confirm your eligibility for the fund, including a personal statement, letter of motivation, letter of recommendation, and a CV.<\/li>\n<li><strong>Admission Requirements: To be<\/strong> admitted to the master\u2019s degree program, claimants must hold a first-class honours degree at the UG level and meet the <b>university&#8217;s entry requirements<\/b>.<\/li>\n<li><strong>Language Requirement:\u00a0<\/strong>If your first language is not English, you must provide proof of your English proficiency before being admitted to a postgraduate course.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h3 id=\"application-deadline\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Application_Deadline\"><\/span><strong>Application Deadline:<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>The last date to apply for the <strong>University of Bradford Scholarship<\/strong> for International Students differs for every scholarship.<\/p>\n<h3 id=\"how-to-apply-for-the-university-of-bradford-scholarship\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"How_to_Apply_for_the_University_of_Bradford_Scholarship\"><\/span><strong>How to Apply for the University of Bradford Scholarship?<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><strong>Every Scholarship has its method of application.<\/strong> Visit the scholarship link given above for more details about how to apply for the University of Bradford Scholarship. To be considered for the University of Bradford Scholarship education award, claimants must be enrolled in the <strong>postgraduate degree coursework<\/strong>. After getting confirmation, they can complete the <strong>online application form<\/strong> for this grant. The application link and Official Website link are given below:<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"Yes, you can apply for the International Scholarship financed by the University of Bradford if you cannot pay&hellip;\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":18371,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"footnotes":""},"categories":[14],"tags":[904],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/applyjobs.org.ng\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/9119"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/applyjobs.org.ng\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/applyjobs.org.ng\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/applyjobs.org.ng\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/applyjobs.org.ng\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=9119"}],"version-history":[{"count":2,"href":"https:\/\/applyjobs.org.ng\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/9119\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":18372,"href":"https:\/\/applyjobs.org.ng\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/9119\/revisions\/18372"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/applyjobs.org.ng\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media\/18371"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/applyjobs.org.ng\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=9119"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":